-- Sino Land unit's HK$730 mln bid wins Hong Kong land auction 
-- By Yimou Lee and Christina Lo
-- Mon Sep 29, 2014 06:50AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Sept 29 (Reuters) - A unit of Hong Kong developer Sino Land Co Ltd <0083.HK> won an auction for a residential site with a HK$730 million ($94 million) bid, the government said on Monday.

Sino Land's unit Bright Land Development Ltd outbid 22 other developers, such as Li Ka-shing's Cheung Kong (Holdings) Ltd <0001.HK> and Sun Hung Kai Properties Ltd <0016.HK>, for the site located in the Fanling district of the New Territories.  The 2,828 square metres site will have at least 250 residential units and a public car park, the government said.